# Routing

Routes are declared in `apps/web/src/router.tsx` via `createBrowserRouter`.

## Public routes

- `/` — Landing page
- `/courses` — Course index
- `/courses/:slug` — Course detail (uses `currentVersion` when version omitted)
- `/courses/:slug/:version` — Course detail for a specific version (e.g. `v1`, `v2`)

## Course slugs

- `quran-tajweed`
- `super-mom-parenting`

## Lesson route

```
/courses/:slug/:version/modules/:moduleNumber/lessons/:lessonSlug
```

- `:lessonSlug` is `<lessonNumber>-<token>` (e.g. `1-a8f3k2q1`)
- Each available lesson has a stable `token` in course content (`apps/web/src/content/courses/`)
- The lesson page resolves only when module number, lesson number, and token all match
- Numeric-only slugs (e.g. `/lessons/2`) return NotFound
- The `:version` segment is **mandatory** so v1 students keep v1 URLs forever

## Lesson access gating

- Course-page lesson links open a password modal before navigation (`LessonGateModal`)
- Password is read from `VITE_LESSON_GATE_PASSWORD` (see `apps/web/.env.example`)
- Shared lesson URLs are public — anyone with the full token-bearing link can view without a password

## Navigation rules

- Use `<Link>` from `react-router-dom` for internal navigation — not raw `<a href>` for in-app routes
- Lesson links from the course curriculum use a button + password gate, not a direct `<Link>`
- Landing section anchors: `<Link to="/#about">` etc.; `LandingPage` scrolls to hash on mount
- Register-interest form opens WhatsApp (`wa.me`) with pre-filled course details; number in `siteCopy.footer.whatsAppNumber`
